usig2.jpg"><br><br><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/userinfo.html?char=87761">My Equipment</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CAD5D8><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub75.ezboard.com/ulathyris.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lathyris</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Deviaant</span><br>  Posts: 77<br> <font color=#333333>(9/18/02 7:16:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub75.ezboard.com/ftrk72095frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=964.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What Sony Doesn't Want You To Know</span><hr size=1> A hoax...? Looks like they're just trying to cover their arses to me. I dunno, because I haven't petitioned in a long time either, but I don't believe I've ever heard anything good about the CS when one does. The one time I actually did, I was astounded by the rudeness and childishness of the guide when he finally got around to responding to me a few days later.<br>Anyway, that's not what I came in to say. I came to say... Blizzard has never let me down before, Sony has let me down countless times. IF I sink to the level of getting addicted to another one of these brain suckers, it'll be World of Warcraft, hands down. Sony's games aren't even an option. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CAD5D8><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub75.ezboard.com/ualundraadjani.showPublicProfile?language=EN>AlundraAdjani</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.theroyalknights.org/sigs/kittenicon.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Saucy Kitty</span><br>  Posts: 5675<br> <font color=#333333>(9/18/02 8:03:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub75.ezboard.com/ftrk72095frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=964.topic&index=7>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.theroyalknights.org/sigs/nowhining.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What Sony Doesn't Want You To Know</span><hr size=1> I agree, I think they are still treating us like the suckers they obviously view us as being, and seeing just how much BS they can feed us that we'll buy.<br><br>If the chick's post is true, she was demoted and eventually kicked out of the guide program altogether for not keeping her mouth shut about what she learned.  It would not be a stretch of reason to think they will lie about it publicly to keep it under wraps.  They probably, if asked, would deny she had ever been a guide at all.  But I have seen and heard too much from verant to think anything of this sort is above them. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CAD5D8><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub75.ezboard.com/uharrah.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Harrah</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>peep</span><br>  Posts: 316<br> <font color=#333333>(9/19/02 11:37:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub75.ezboard.com/ftrk72095frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=964.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.bellsouth.net/coDataImages/bellsouthpwp/Groups/6/6185/pages/15262/BRock.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What Sony Doesn't Want You To Know</span><hr size=1> Verant/SOE bad CS is NOT a hoax.  What I see there with their hasty issue of statement is that they got caught with their pants down.  Sure, it may never be their intent to do away with free (no actually, we pay for it every month =p) CS, that guide gal may have drawn the extrapolation a touch too far.  Verant/SOE does not want to spend the money for better CS.  Count on it.  I think guides &amp; GMs quit because it is too stressful.  There is no definite hierarchy for issue solution, because rot at the core spreads outward.  The higher ups never planned for CS and the issues that come with MMORPGs.  Get their money first is the tenant; patch it up with bubblegum and bailing wire later.<br><br>Sometimes I wonder why I keep playing this fool game <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CAD5D8><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub75.ezboard.com/utrilobate.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Trilo Bate</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>;announce camper</span><br>  Posts: 383<br> <font color=#333333>(9/19/02 1:25:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub75.ezboard.com/ftrk72095frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=964.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What Sony Doesn't Want You To Know</span><hr size=1> I did not certify that it was a hoax.<br><br>I was merely pointing out that Verant answered this one VERY quickly. As with everything in RL...We will see.<br><br>Melo / Rezann understands that we don't believe everything we are told (even from the horse's mouth). You filter out the predictions and analyse the facts that have actually occurred.<br><br>For my part, I have /petitioned twice for minor stuff and have had answers both times. The service was also courteous. One of the petitions took a couple hours to get a response, but I did get a polite response.<br><br><!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>&quot;Behind every great fortune is a crime&quot; <p>Trilo Bate 55 Druid <BR>Repro Bate 36 Druid <BR>Proud Member of The Royal Knights</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CAD5D8><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub75.ezboard.com/uraethorn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Raethorn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Raethong</span><br>  Posts: 1311<br> <font color=#333333>(9/19/02 3:06:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub75.ezboard.com/ftrk72095frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=964.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What Sony Doesn't Want You To Know</span><hr size=1> I have petitioned somewhere from three to five times in Raethorns career. Each one has taken longer and been less courteous then the previous time. My experiences havent been really terrible (although I can't understand why my epic couldn't have been restored) but I have heard some stories. I also should say that I think my faction was lowered with the GM's because I was given a soulmark(or something), wonder if I still have that. I was very pleased with the result of my first petition way back at level 25 or something. Well, enough with my babbling. My view reflects Harrah's mostly but I can't be too disappointed if I don't expect much. <p><p><center><img src = http://nilsig.homestead.com/files/Raetseig.gif></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CAD5D8><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub75.ezboard.com/ubruujo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bruujo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Nook happy!</span><br>  Posts: 261<br> <font color=#333333>(9/19/02 7:36:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub75.ezboard.com/ftrk72095frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=964.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What Sony Doesn't Want You To Know</span><hr size=1> Soulmarks are permanent.  If they put it in your file, every guide/senior/gm that takes a petition from you or even sees you can look it up, even if it was given to you at level 1.  It's not normal policy to look up soulmarks, however, unless an issue comes up that either requires a soulmark to be placed on the character, such as item reimbursal, or if a disruption is dealt with, in which case, they check 